LDTEXT:
@03:42 - ROC called for outlet free chlorine high alarm
Reviewed trends, chlorine analyzer had spiked to 5 mg/L twice in the past hour.  Analyzer was reading 5 mg/L from 03:34 to 03:44, and has been steadily dropping since.  Coincides with when the ROC started filling the tower

@04:02 - Deactivated duty to see if the alarm comes back with the tower draining.  Analyzer reading spiked slightly, but then stabilized at ~1.65 mg/L around 04:40.  

Requested ROC to call back if the outlet FCL goes high again, and will attend site at that point.

ROC called regarding settled water conduit lolo alarms, as well as CO2 adjusted pH low alarm.  
@15:36 - CO2 adjusted Low alarm, which stopped the low lift pumps, causing the settled water lolo alarms to follow @15:41
@15:49 when ROC called, CO2 adjusted pH had recovered.  Was able to clear alarms and Low lifts restarted, filling the pretreatment / settled water conduit 
Monitored site remotely, everything is back to normal operations as of @16:00
